"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144779","Northern Ireland Office","false","2019-09-09","<p>This is a devolved matter in Northern Ireland, and as such is the responsibility of the Department for Infrastructure. Information can be requested from the Permanent Secretary at DfI.</p>","Skipton and Ripon","Julian Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144779/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T13:11:18.637Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144779/answer","Biography information for Julian Smith","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144779/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2019-09-04","Blue Badge Scheme: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, if he will increase the health conditions criteria for qualification under the blue badge scheme.","false","Biography information for Paul Girvan","South Antrim","Paul Girvan","286856"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144780","Department for Transport","false","2019-09-09","<p>Eligibility for a blue badge is not restricted to specific conditions. People with Chron's Disease and other Inflammatory bowel disease conditions could receive a badge if they meet the eligibility criteria. The aim of the new expanded criteria is to ensure that those with non-visible conditions with the greatest needs have equal access to badges.</p><p> </p><p>It is for the relevant local authority to decide if an applicant meets the eligibility criteria.</p><p> </p>","Wealden","Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144780/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T15:55:19.55Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144780/answer","Biography information for Ms Nusrat Ghani","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144780/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-09-04","Blue Badge Scheme: Inflammatory Bowel Disease","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will make an assessment of the potential merits of expanding the Blue Badge Scheme to include people with (a) Chron's Disease and (b) other Inflammatory bowel disease conditions.","false","Biography information for Paul Girvan","South Antrim","Paul Girvan","286857"
