"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144806","Treasury","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Chancellor announced at the recent Spending Round that we will provide £160m to the Scottish Government in 2020-21 in relation to historic allocations of Common Agricultural Policy ‘convergence’ funding. The additional funding will be ring-fenced for farmers and land managers in Scotland. The review led by Lord Bew of Donegore has considered a separate but related matter.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144806/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T09:17:35.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144806/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144806/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-09-04","Agriculture: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the £160 million announced in Spending Round 2019 as a result of the Bew Review will be ringfenced for agriculture so that the Scottish Parliament can decide how it is allocated within that sector.","false","Biography information for Luke Graham","Ochil and South Perthshire","Luke Graham","286834"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144807","Home Office","false","2019-09-09","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</p>","Louth and Horncastle","Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144807/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T16:47:52.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144807/answer","Biography information for Victoria Atkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144807/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-09-04","Asylum: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps her Department is taking to ensure people who are in receipt of Section 4 support are able to cover (a) travel fares which can only be purchased with cash and (b) other upfront travel costs in order to report at Home Office reporting centres.","false","Biography information for Ruth Smeeth","Stoke-on-Trent North","Ruth Smeeth","286814"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144808","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Department fully understands that maintaining access to Seretide inhalers for the management of asthma is vitally important to many people in this country. We are currently not aware of any supply issues with Seretide inhalers from GSK and they are available in volumes sufficient to meet normal United Kingdom demand.</p><p>We continue to work closely with industry and partners in the health system to help prevent shortages and to ensure that the risks to patients are minimised when supply issues do arise.</p>","Bury St Edmunds","Jo Churchill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144808/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T15:12:03.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144808/answer","Biography information for Jo Churchill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144808/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-09-04","Seretide","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what assessment he has made of the availability of the asthma drug serotide in pharmacies; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","286679"
