"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144816","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-09-09","<p>Around five Army recruits undergoing basic training are currently recorded as on &quot;sick leave&quot;, where they have been off training for more than 14 days. The number has been rounded to the nearest five to limit disclosure and ensure confidentiality. It is drawn from single service sources rather than official statistics produced by Defence Statistics.</p>","Plymouth, Moor View","Johnny Mercer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144816/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T16:01:07.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144816/answer","Biography information for Johnny Mercer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144816/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-09-04","Army: Sick Leave","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many army recruits are on sick leave.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","286786"
