"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144823","Treasury","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Government will set out details of the review shortly.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144823/answer",,,,,"286783","2019-09-09T12:53:38.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144823/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144823/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-09-04","Tax Avoidance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, with reference to the oral contribution of the Prime Minister of 4 September 2019, what steps he plans to take to ensure that a review into the 2019 Loan Charge is independent of (a) his Department and (b) HMRC.","false","Biography information for Ruth Cadbury","Brentford and Isleworth","Ruth Cadbury","286781"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144824","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-09-09","<p>Wait times vary by establishment. Wait times for access to military primary care rehabilitation facilities or to a routine medical appointment range from same day to 48 hours. Those recorded on the Wounded, Injured, &amp; Long Term Sick Management Information System (WISMIS) are normally seen on the same day. Secondary healthcare services are provided by the NHS and information on wait times is not held centrally by the Ministry of Defence.</p>","Plymouth, Moor View","Johnny Mercer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144824/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T15:54:03.217Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144824/answer","Biography information for Johnny Mercer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144824/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-09-04","Army: Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the average wait is for army recruits reporting health issues during their training to receive medical treatment from (a) primary care services and (b) secondary care services.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","286788"
