"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144381","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-09-09","<p>The number of bids received by the Department and NHS England and NHS Improvement for capital spending are not held centrally and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144381/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T14:24:21.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144381/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144381/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-09-03","NHS: Capital Investment","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many bids for capital spending has (a) his Department and (b) NHS England received from NHS organisations in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Sir George Howarth","Knowsley","Sir George Howarth","286113"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144382","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-09-09","<p>The number of civilian and military personnel based in the UK and Saudi Arabia who were employed by the Saudi Arabian National Guard Communications Project (SANGCOM) and the Ministry of Defence Saudi Armed Forces Projects (MODSAP) on 1 April 2019 is shown below. The Saudi Arabian Government reimburses the UK Ministry of Defence for these staff costs and there is, therefore, no cost to the UK taxpayer.</p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Manpower number as at 1 April 2019</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>SANGCOM</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>MODSAP</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>UK-based Civilian Staff</p></td><td><p>4</p></td><td><p>69</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>UK-based Military Staff</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>35</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Saudi-based Civilian Staff</p></td><td><p>51</p></td><td><p>38</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Saudi-based Military Staff</p></td><td><p>20</p></td><td><p>66</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144382/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T15:13:23.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144382/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144382/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-09-03","Ministry of Defence: Saudi Arabia","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) civilian staff in his Department based in the UK, (b) military personnel based in the UK, (c) civilian staff in his Department based in Saudi Arabia and (d) military personnel based in Saudi Arabia were employed by the (i) Saudi Arabian National Guard Communications Project and (ii) Ministry of Defence Saudi Armed Forces Project on 1 April 2019.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","286284"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144383","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-09-09","<p>The expenditure of the Saudi Arabian National Guard Communications Project (SANGCOM) is recovered from the Saudi Arabian Government, but SANGCOM operates under a separate Memorandum of Understanding from Ministry of Defence Saudi Armed Forces Project (MODSAP), under which the details of such recoveries are confidential to the two Governments.</p><p>The expenditure by the MODSAP in financial year 2018-19 amounted to £66.43 million. The budget however for financial year 2019-20 is £69.08 million. The costs of MODSAP are met from a management fee received from the Saudi Arabian Government.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144383/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T15:09:28.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144383/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144383/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-09-03","Saudi Arabia: Military Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the (a) expenditure was for the financial year 2018-19 and (b) budget is for 2019-20 for (i) the Saudi Arabian National Guard Communications Project and (ii) the Ministry of Defence Saudi Armed Forces Project.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","286285"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144384","Treasury","false","2019-09-09","<p>The UK’s Crown Dependencies and Overseas Territories are self-governing jurisdictions with their own democratically-elected governments responsible for most areas of their domestic policy, including fiscal matters. They co-operate with the UK in matters relating to taxation, fighting financial crime and countering terrorist finance.</p><p> </p><p>The Crown Dependencies and Overseas Territories have committed to meeting the global standards for anti-money laundering and counter terrorist financing set by the Financial Action Task Force (FATF). They are evaluated by the FATF in their own rights as self-governing jurisdictions.</p><p> </p><p>The Crown Dependencies and Overseas Territories with financial centres share beneficial ownership information with the UK’s law enforcement agencies and are committed to global tax transparency standards such as the OECD Common Reporting Standard, an agreement to automatically exchange financial account information with other jurisdictions.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144384/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T13:58:35.707Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144384/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144384/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-09-03","Money Laundering: British Overseas Territories and Crown Dependencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what steps his Department is taking to (a) tackle Money Laundering and (b) promote ethical financing in the Crown Dependencies and the UK’s Overseas Territories.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","286286"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144385","Treasury","false","2019-09-09","<p>The government assesses a range of money laundering and terrorist financing risks to the UK through the joint Treasury and Home Office National Risk Assessment (NRA). This includes considering risks in other jurisdictions that may facilitate money laundering or terrorist financing activity in the UK. The last NRA was published in October 2017 and can be found here: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-risk-assessment-of-money-laundering-and-terrorist-financing-2017" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/national-risk-assessment-of-money-laundering-and-terrorist-financing-2017</a>. The next NRA will be published by July 2020.</p>","Salisbury","John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144385/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T12:49:09.58Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144385/answer","Biography information for John Glen","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144385/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2019-09-03","Money Laundering: British Overseas Territories and Crown Dependencies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment his Department has made of the potential risk of the misuse of financial investment treaties to launder money in the Crown Dependencies and the UK’s Overseas Territories.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","286287"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144386","Department for Transport","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Government has charged Douglas Oakervee to consider these matters as part of the Review that is now underway. This will consider its benefits and impacts; affordability and efficiency; deliverability; and scope and phasing. The terms of reference include consideration of the direct cost of reprioritising, cancelling or de-scoping the project, including contractual penalties and supply chain impact.</p><p> </p><p>The Government will consider the Review’s findings in the autumn.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144386/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T14:14:51.66Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144386/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144386/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-09-03","High Speed Two","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the contractual (a) terms and (b) liabilities HS2 Ltd has with its (i) contractors and (ii) consultants in advance of the decision to review High Speed Two.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","286252"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144387","Department for Transport","false","2019-09-09","<p>The Department has not assessed the additional costs for cancelling the competition but they are envisaged to be small.</p>","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144387/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T16:08:07.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144387/answer","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144387/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-09-03","South Eastern Rail Franchise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what additional costs were incurred to the public purse as a result of the cancellation of the South Eastern rail franchise.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","286253"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144388","Department for Transport","false","2019-09-09","<p>As set out in the Invitation to Tender (ITT) for the South Eastern Franchise, the Secretary of State reserves the right to cancel the competition and he has elected to exercise that right in respect of the South Eastern Franchise competition.</p><p>Given this, and as particularised at paragraph 1.9 of the ITT, the Department does not accept that bidders are entitled to any reimbursement of their bid costs.</p>","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144388/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T13:42:28.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144388/answer","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144388/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-09-03","South Eastern Rail Franchise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what estimate has he made of potential bidding costs companies will be entitled to claim from his Department as a result of the decision to cancel the South Eastern Rail franchise competition.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","286254"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144389","Department for Transport","false","2019-09-09","<p>Officials have met representatives from Govia and Abellio to discuss feedback on the quality of their bids.</p>","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144389/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T16:20:56.387Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144389/answer","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144389/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-09-03","South Eastern Rail Franchise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what meetings he has had held with (a) Govia and (b) Abellio on the cancellation of the South Eastern rail franchise competition.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","286255"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144390","Department for Transport","false","2019-09-09","<p>Following the cancellation of the South Eastern Franchise competition, the Department is developing proposals for the franchise. This will include routes to increase rolling stock capacity.</p>","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144390/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T13:50:09.923Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144390/answer","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144390/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-09-03","South Eastern Rail Franchise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the timeframe is for the introduction of new rolling stock on the south eastern rail route following the decision to cancel the franchise competition.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","286256"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144391","Department for Transport","false","2019-09-09","<p>Since the Review started in September 2018, Keith Williams has held regular meetings with the Department.</p><p> </p>","Daventry","Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144391/answer",,,,,,"2019-09-09T13:44:56.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144391/answer","Biography information for Chris Heaton-Harris","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1144391/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2019-09-03","South Eastern Rail Franchise","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what discussions took place between his Department and the Government Rail Review chair Keith Williams prior to his Department's decision to cancel the South Eastern rail franchise competition.","false","Biography information for Andy McDonald","Middlesbrough","Andy McDonald","286257"
